# Flutter Local-First Rules

## UI and State

- Follow the existing Flutter structure under `lib/presentation`, `lib/domain`, and `lib/data`.
- Put screens in `lib/presentation/screens`.
- Keep widget code readable for workshop learners.
- Use existing Provider-based patterns unless the user explicitly asks to change state management.
- Keep UI copy in Hong Kong Traditional Chinese where user-visible.

## Local Data

- Core expense data should work locally first.
- Use the existing repository/data-source pattern.
- Do not require Supabase for adding, listing, reporting, or exporting local expenses.
- If adding fields to expenses, update entity, local data source, repository mapping, and relevant tests together.

## Device Capabilities

- OCR/photo/camera features belong to the rich client.
- Prefer device OCR for basic receipt text extraction because it is cheaper and privacy-friendly.
- Always leave a manual fallback when OCR fails.

## AI Features in Flutter

- Flutter may call app-level AI abstractions, but should not call OpenRouter, DeepSeek, OpenAI, or other LLM APIs directly.
- Flutter should call Vercel API endpoints or demo/mock services.
- Keep demo mode available for workshop Tier A.

## Testing

- Update widget/unit tests when visible text, categories, forms, reports, or navigation change.
- Prefer focused tests for the changed behavior.

